         <abstract>
            <p>This paper formulates a mixed integer linear programming model to find the optimal combination of leveraged leasing parameters that will meet the IRS "qualified lease" requirements and also maximize the net present value of the lease to the lessor. Using the MILP model allows lessors affected by the "at-risk" rule of the Tax Reform Act of 1976 to redesign leases to meet both the qualified lease requirements and the new at-risk rule without reducing the aggregate attractiveness of the lease to either the lessor or the lessee.</p>
         </abstract>
